abstract: It was a week of turmoil, but it seemed to prove an immutable rule of the Trump presidency: People see what they want to see, even if others see something very different.
snippet: It was a week of turmoil, but it seemed to prove an immutable rule of the Trump presidency: People see what they want to see, even if others see something very different.
lead_paragraph: For Parson Hicks, a health care finance executive who supports President Trump, this past week has felt a little like déjà vu. Mr. Trump says something. His opponents howl and then predict, with certainty, a point of no return.

abstract: The dead and injured represented 34 nationalities, including a Belgian mother, an Italian father and an American.
snippet: The dead and injured represented 34 nationalities, including a Belgian mother, an Italian father and an American.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — A Belgian mother was killed while on holiday with her husband and two young sons. So was an Italian father, as he held the hand of his 5-year-old son.

abstract: I supported the president in dozens of articles, radio and TV appearances. I won’t do it any longer.
snippet: I supported the president in dozens of articles, radio and TV appearances. I won’t do it any longer.
lead_paragraph: When Donald Trump first announced his presidential campaign, I, like most people, thought it would be a short-lived publicity stunt. A month later, though, I happened to catch one of his political rallies on C-Span. I was riveted.

headline_main: Summer Reading Contest Winner, Week 7 | On ‘I Don’t Want to Watch Slavery Fan Fiction’

abstract: A statement from the White House, under siege over President Trump’s initial comments, on Sunday condemned “white supremacists” for inciting violence that left a woman dead.
snippet: A statement from the White House, under siege over President Trump’s initial comments, on Sunday condemned “white supremacists” for inciting violence that left a woman dead.
lead_paragraph: BRIDGEWATER, N.J. — White House officials, under siege over President Trump’s reluctance to condemn white supremacists for the weekend’s bloody rallies in Charlottesville, Va., tried to clarify his comments on Sunday, as critics in both parties intensified demands that he adopt a stronger, more unifying message.

abstract: Faust made a better bargain than Donald Trump’s vice president did.
snippet: Faust made a better bargain than Donald Trump’s vice president did.
lead_paragraph: The other day, from the Naval Observatory in Washington, you heard a howl of such volume and anguish that it cracked mirrors and sent small forest animals scurrying for cover. Vice President Mike Pence was furious. He was offended. Someone — namely, my Times colleagues Jonathan Martin and Alexander Burns — had dared to call him out on the fact that he seemed to be laying the groundwork for a presidential bid.

abstract: Every month, Netflix Canada adds a new batch of movies and TV shows to its libraries. Here are the titles we think are most interesting this month.

lead_paragraph: Every month, Netflix Canada adds a new batch of movies and TV shows to its libraries. Here are the titles we think are most interesting, broken down by release date. Netflix occasionally changes schedules without giving notice. (Unfortunately, streaming information provided in our Watchlist listings applies only to viewers in the United States.)

abstract: Despite a re-election mandate, Iran’s moderate president seems unlikely to fulfill a campaign promise to appoint women to his cabinet.
snippet: Despite a re-election mandate, Iran’s moderate president seems unlikely to fulfill a campaign promise to appoint women to his cabinet.
lead_paragraph: TEHRAN — President Hassan Rouhani, endorsed by Iran’s supreme leader on Thursday with a nationally televised cheek-kiss, is starting his second term under newly intense pressure from both hard-line opponents and many of his own reform-minded supporters.
